JOHANNESBURG South African Communist Party (SACP) general-secretary Blade Nzimande is delivering the Chris Hani memorial in Durban. The SACP is holding memorials around the country to honour the struggle icon.Hani was gunned down by white nationalists outside his Boksburg home in the run up to the country s first democratic elections.WATCH: Remembering Chris HaniPolish immigrant and anti-communist Janusz Walu shot Hani while he was walking home from a morning jog.ANC secretary general, Gwede Mantashe is also addressing the Hani memorial in Klerksdorp in North West.eNCA